<subSubSection id="B8840A0B5602DAFCA2E9A2453AACA0E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="096A35DD1FB04003122CB2565930FA40" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="281ABD02894F612DEF0882482322B1C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">In full-face view, lateral margin of head anterior to eye level diverging posteriorly; anterior clypeal margin truncate; no white spot on dorsum of second and third abdominal tergites; body color black; antennal scape without erect hairs, propodeal dorsum slightly concave.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66D8C8CDB37A349CE4877DDD108C3471" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5A6C7E3071CF9F99CF47B9B7A19793B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="02745717C10B3B3F4CDE0BEC705B04FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
See the geographic distribution and biology in 
<bibRefCitation id="5E791E1507DF34A3A92418870E329B32" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" author="Rakotonirina, JC" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="001 - 058" refId="B30" refString="Rakotonirina, JC, Fisher, BL, 2018. Taxonomic revision of the Malagasy Camponotus subgenus Mayria (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) using qualitative and quantitative morphology. Zootaxa 4438 (1): 001 - 058, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" title="Taxonomic revision of the Malagasy Camponotus subgenus Mayria (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) using qualitative and quantitative morphology." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" volume="4438" year="2018">Rakotonirina and Fisher (2018)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="107117A952D0541CDBD01E3B575A3C1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4AB05873BA95655979EBC7F59B30A520" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C7C0425CBDCF05098058804D2582DB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="0FC0988500BF0471E078187902AD2A50" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1886" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus lubbocki" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lubbocki">
<emphasis id="1DC83510166171469B3C09F51F7FD815" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Camponotus lubbocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="B1A30B0F9F86D763AFE81AE4F3433F1C" genus="C." lsidName="C. liandia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="liandia">
<emphasis id="D60C85EDA690D102E7928C62346DF2BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. liandia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the latter has a broadly convex anteromedian margin of the clypeus. It looks similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9F63261290AA3F28812AABC3C21A9980" genus="C." lsidName="C. immaculatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="immaculatus">
<emphasis id="AF3C0E5113D6EC6A44AC1D591DE1CE8C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. immaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="87A925E3C7816F250385ECE8319D2243" genus="C." lsidName="C. kelimaso" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kelimaso">
<emphasis id="34FD7FB3D6910D376AAEED78FE29E0AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. kelimaso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they too lack white spots on the second and third abdominal segments, but in 
<taxonomicName id="CC7D7BD5E8BEC5B2B21790447BCE8FD8" genus="C." lsidName="C. immaculatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="immaculatus">
<emphasis id="675A7A99A46269CC35B25CBBE3E86194" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. immaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the propodeal dorsum is transversely concave and in 
<taxonomicName id="B63E1EAEF6F63EDBFC6E7D7BFD6F0341" genus="C." lsidName="C. kelimaso" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kelimaso">
<emphasis id="B07D4AC27D7249B8FD2607D521FBF7C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. kelimaso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the eyes are small and the posterior cephalic margin is approximately straight.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F6DA45B26C29337A022E67FE46C5B4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="AB99FC140C307021C41FA870BE2ABDEE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.19251" author="Forel, A" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="59 - 92" refId="B22" refString="Forel, A, 1912. Formicides neotropiques. Part VI. 5eme sous-famille Camponotinae Forel. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique 20: 59 - 92, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.19251" title="Formicides neotropiques. Part VI. 5 eme sous-famille Camponotinae Forel." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.19251" volume="20" year="1912">Forel (1912)</bibRefCitation>
originally placed 
<taxonomicName id="6839CFEEF65ECE2A2C4E094F06C1F887" genus="C." lsidName="C. lubbocki" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lubbocki">
<emphasis id="7E03A6278EA2983623B3CFD34D624373" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. lubbocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="49FAA6DAD320B0B7C94E176D3C6BABEB" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus (Myrmosaga)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Myrmosaga">Camponotus Myrmosaga</taxonomicName>
, which was later synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E4C7F36DD22F5E4D0C122E0AE31A35C" author="Emery, C" journalOrPublisher="Genera Insectorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 302" refId="B11" refString="Emery, C, 1925. Hymenoptera. Fam. Formicidae. Subfam. Formicinae. Genera Insectorum 183: 1 - 302" title="Hymenoptera. Fam. Formicidae. Subfam. Formicinae." volume="183" year="1925">Emery (1925)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName id="86AF1C02C43F5BD4F5CE83B213CAE1D1" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Mayria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mayria" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3AC8B06E5310F631538A4FFE771E734C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mayria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation id="BE609DAE7DEBCC84237CD09322E0B621" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" author="Rakotonirina, JC" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="001 - 058" refId="B30" refString="Rakotonirina, JC, Fisher, BL, 2018. Taxonomic revision of the Malagasy Camponotus subgenus Mayria (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) using qualitative and quantitative morphology. Zootaxa 4438 (1): 001 - 058, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" title="Taxonomic revision of the Malagasy Camponotus subgenus Mayria (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) using qualitative and quantitative morphology." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" volume="4438" year="2018">Rakotonirina and Fisher 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Whereas this species was recently redescribed under 
<taxonomicName id="6111886F8B822F842119CD30E21861F0" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Mayria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mayria" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C18F7E8E40DEB90E1CDC709CDF1ADEA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mayria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is morphologically similar to those within 
<taxonomicName id="6091227ED3B76A945A9B47E7837CF374" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmosaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Myrmosaga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="027BB20BBDE816095D5C7C987CC8FAFC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Myrmosaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its broadly projected rectangular clypeus that is medially carinate, and a more or less anteroposteriorly flattened petiolar node. The subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="E40392B70453D7D9D394E56A2D131EA1" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus (Mayria)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mayria">Camponotus Mayria</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the clypeus that has no median carina, but with a rounded anterior margin, and a nodiform petiole. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="1477DF4542E63599D696DD3B7E24ED3B" genus="C." lsidName="C. lubbocki" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lubbocki">
<emphasis id="5401A6A6CF1C2D5665A040C101DB8624" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. lubbocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is moved back to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4178D7271478BE851FEE6314475010AA" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Camponotus (Myrmosaga)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Myrmosaga">Camponotus Myrmosaga</taxonomicName>
here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A566B62CB9883C0C05AE5D03E4DA756" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species delimitation of 
<taxonomicName id="06EDDE48C446CD84883351CABD81AE71" genus="C." lsidName="C. lubbocki" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lubbocki">
<emphasis id="D66C731B4BC66C9FA49E38E6A43F3E93" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C. lubbocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on qualitative morphology is sustained by the NC-clustering method. Identification of this species is confirmed by LDA with 100% success (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="88D62156956E4D1610576CE8B3C9045C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" author="Rakotonirina, JC" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="001 - 058" refId="B30" refString="Rakotonirina, JC, Fisher, BL, 2018. Taxonomic revision of the Malagasy Camponotus subgenus Mayria (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) using qualitative and quantitative morphology. Zootaxa 4438 (1): 001 - 058, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" title="Taxonomic revision of the Malagasy Camponotus subgenus Mayria (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) using qualitative and quantitative morphology." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4438.1.1" volume="4438" year="2018">Rakotonirina and Fisher 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
